          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Measurement of fission excitation functions in 11B,",
                " 16O,19F+232Th reactions in the extreme sub-barrier",
                " energy region"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "D.M.Nadkarni",
                "A.Saxena",
                "D.C.Biswas",
                "R.K.Choudhury",
                "S.S.Kapoor",
                "N.Majumdar",
                "P.Bhattacharya"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "3INDTRM",
                "3INDSAH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,PR/C,59,R580,1999",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,PR/C,59,R580,1999",
                    "doi": "10.1103/PhysRevC.59.R580",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "PR/C",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "59",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "R580"
                      },
                      "date": 1999
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "3INDTAT"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " BARC-TIFR 14UD Pelletron accelerator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A self supporting 1.8 mg/cm**2 thick 232Th target"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PS",
                "MWPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two low pressure X-Y position sensitive",
                " multiwire avalanche counters of Breskin-type, having",
                " active dimensions of 6.5 cm x 5.0 cm and 15 cm x",
                " 3.5 cm, were mounted on either side of the fissile",
                " target for detecting the complementary fission",
                " fragments in coincidence.",
                "The position sensitive detectors were kept at 14 cm",
                " and 12 cm, respectively, from the target subtending",
                " the in-plane angles of about 26 deg and 63 deg,",
                " respectively, at the target.",
                "The detectors were moved to different specified angles",
                " (33 deg, 200 deg), (75 deg, 253 deg) with respect to",
                " beam direction to carry out the measurements over a",
                " large angular range.",
                "The detectors were operated with isobutane gas at torr",
                " pressure.                   D6125  1   30"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A 500 micron-thick semiconductor detector was",
                " placed at 25 deg at a distance of 40 cm from the",
                " target to monitor the elastically scattered heavy",
                " ions for normalization purposes."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fusion-fission and transfer fission events",
                " were separated by folding angle technique and the",
                " fission cross sections have been measured employing",
                " the kinematic coincidence.",
                "The time of arrival of the fragments at the two",
                " position sensitive detectors and the X and Y position",
                " pulses from the two detectors were recorded event by",
                " event in list mode."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "INTAD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The angle calibration of the fission fragment",
                " detectors was achieved from the observed dips in the",
                " fragment yields in the detectors due to the shadowing",
                " caused by the wires used to support the thin windows",
                " of the PSDs.",
                "This calibration was done using a 252Cf source mounted",
                " at the point of the target location.",
                "The coincidence timing information from the two",
                " fission fragment detectors was recorded as one of the",
                " parameters to select the genuine fission events time",
                " difference between the two FFs <20 ns and thus helped",
                " to reject random coincidences.",
                "From the event-by-event information on the position of",
                " the two complementary fragments in the two detectors,",
                " their angles of emission were calculated.",
                "The measured folding angle distributions at different",
                " bombarding energies were fitted with three",
                " Gaussian peaks corresponding to fusion-fission,",
                " transfer fission and low momentum transfer fission",
                " events."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
